-- White House mulls dropping bank tax in bill: sources
-- 
-- Tue Jun 29, 2010 12:27pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/06/29/us-financial-regulation-banktax-idUSTRE65S4CF20100629

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - The White House is mulling dropping a controversial tax on financial institutions that has become a sticking point in gaining the needed 60 votes to push the financial regulatory overhaul through the Senate, three sources familiar with the talks said on Tuesday. 

